<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-04-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-04-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="482" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d482">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Terrell</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States.</hi><lb/><hi rend="italic">Constantinople</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-04-27"><hi rend="italic">April 27, 1895</hi></date>.
                                (Received May 13.)</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 526.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inclose herewith the
                            copy of a resolution of thanks passed by the faculty of the American
                            College for Girls in Constantinople on the 5th instant.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">A. W. Terrell.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                        <frus:attachment>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure in No. 526.]</seg></opener>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Mrs. <persName type="from">Dodd</persName> to Mr.
                                        <persName type="to">Terrell</persName>.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American College for Girls</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Constantinople</hi></placeName>[, <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content" calendar="gregorian" type="content-date" when="1895-04-05">undated</date>].</dateline></opener>
                            <p>At a meeting of the faculty of the American College for Girls in
                                Constantinople, held on the 5th of April, 1895, the following
                                resolution was passed: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                    <p>Whereas, the American College for Girls has received from His
                                        Imperial Majesty the Sultan of Turkey an irade, by which all
                                        taxes are forever remitted upon the property of the
                                        college,</p>
                                    <p><hi rend="italic">Resolved</hi>, That the faculty express
                                        their sincere gratitude to the Hon. A. W. Terrell, minister
                                        plenipotentiary of the United States, for his untiring and
                                        successful efforts to obtain this irade.</p>
                                </quote></p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Isabel F. Dodd</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Secretary of the Faculty.</hi></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </frus:attachment>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>